ABI(bytes32,uint256).notice: Returns the ABI associated with an INS node. Defined in EIP205.

addr(bytes32).notice: Returns the address associated with an INS node.

clearRecords(bytes32).notice: Increments the record version associated with an INS node. May only be called by the owner of that node in the INS registry.

contenthash(bytes32).notice: Returns the contenthash associated with an INS node.

interfaceImplementer(bytes32,bytes4).notice: Returns the address of a contract that implements the specified interface for this name. If an implementer has not been set for this interfaceID and name, the resolver will query the contract at `addr()`. If `addr()` is set, a contract exists at that address, and that contract implements EIP165 and returns `true` for the specified interfaceID, its address will be returned.

name(bytes32).notice: Returns the name associated with an INS node, for reverse records. Defined in EIP181.

pubkey(bytes32).notice: Returns the SECP256k1 public key associated with an INS node. Defined in EIP 619.

setABI(bytes32,uint256,bytes).notice: Sets the ABI associated with an INS node. Nodes may have one ABI of each content type. To remove an ABI, set it to the empty string.

setAddr(bytes32,address).notice: Sets the address associated with an INS node. May only be called by the owner of that node in the INS registry.

setContenthash(bytes32,bytes).notice: Sets the contenthash associated with an INS node. May only be called by the owner of that node in the INS registry.

setInterface(bytes32,bytes4,address).notice: Sets an interface associated with a name. Setting the address to 0 restores the default behaviour of querying the contract at `addr()` for interface support.

setName(bytes32,string).notice: Sets the name associated with an INS node, for reverse records. May only be called by the owner of that node in the INS registry.

setPubkey(bytes32,bytes32,bytes32).notice: Sets the SECP256k1 public key associated with an INS node.

setText(bytes32,string,string).notice: Sets the text data associated with an INS node and key. May only be called by the owner of that node in the INS registry.

text(bytes32,string).notice: Returns the text data associated with an INS node and key.

userdoc.notice: A simple resolver anyone can use; only allows the owner of a node to set its address.
